## Source of Truth

Before ANY change, read:

1. `/docs/features/country-detail-view.md`
2. `/docs/features/_overview.md`

Use `Design.md` (Country Detail View) for layout and tokens.

## Reusable Components

From `/docs/features/country-detail-view.md` — Dependencies on Shared Code:

| Path | Description |
|------|-------------|
| `src/app/components/countryData.ts` | `getCountryData`, `CountryData`, regulation types |
| `src/app/components/flagComponents.tsx` | Large flag display |
| `src/imports/RightVpnFeatures.tsx` | `MapLayerOption` for layer-aware UI |

If a shared component covers 80%+ of the requirement, extend it via props/config. Do NOT fork it. Do NOT create a parallel version.

## Feature-Specific Constraints

- Only countries defined in `countryData.ts` have full detail content; preserve fallback behavior for unknown names.
- Regulatory copy is static demo content, not legal advice.

## Patterns to Follow

- Presentation component: `countryName`, `onBack`, `activeLayer` from parent — no global state.

## What NOT to Do

- Do NOT fork `getCountryData` or duplicate `CountryData` shape — extend `countryData.ts` (requires `shared-policies.mdc` approval for data shape changes).
- Do NOT modify parent routing in `ISPRegulationsPanel.tsx` without coordination.
- Do NOT add routes.
- Do NOT change `CountryData` fields without updating `/docs/features/country-detail-view.md` and `countryData.ts` first.
